</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/CuriousGeorge" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/CuriousGeorge">Curious George</a></em> (based on the PBS Kids show)
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DanielTigersNeighborhood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DanielTigersNeighborhood"> Daniel Tiger's Neighborhood</a></em>
</li><li> <em>Disney Live!</em> (franchise)
<ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SofiaTheFirst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SofiaTheFirst">Sofia the First</a></em> and <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/JakeAndTheNeverLandPirates" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/JakeAndTheNeverLandPirates">Jake and the Never Land Pirates</a></em> were combined for a <em>Disney Junior</em> stage tour called <em>Pirate and Princess Adventures</em>. The pre-show also featured <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DocMcStuffins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DocMcStuffins">Doc McStuffins</a></em>. This later got a sequel called <em>Disney Junior Dance Party</em>, which featured most of the newer shows on the channel.
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DoraTheExplorer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DoraTheExplorer">Dora the Explorer</a></em>
