</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PriPara" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PriPara">PriPara</a></em> has received two of these.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Rugrats" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Rugrats">Rugrats</a></em> as <em>Rugrats: A Live Adventure</em>
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SailorMoon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SailorMoon">Sailor Moon</a></em> (a franchise of "Sailor Moon Musicals" in and of itself; referred to by fans as "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/SeraMyu" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/SeraMyu">Sera Myu</a>" for short. There have also been several costume-character shows that were performed at malls and amusement parks.)
